    <worksheet name='Sheet 9'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='16'>34% of Orders (All Electronics) Fall Below the 25% Margin Line — A Profit Headwind</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>N: 51 out of 150 orders (34%) are below 25% profit margin — all of them Electronics. These orders account for ₹61.02M (91.5% of revenue) but only 72.7% of total profit. R: Electronics drive volume and scale but dilute margin; Software and Accessories punch 5× and 2.5× above their revenue weight in profit. A: Implement a deal‑level margin review: any Electronics quote below 15% margin must include a high‑margin Software attachment (e.g., Antivirus) to reach a blended 20% floor.
</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources>
            <datasource caption='Raw Data (Day88_AdvTableau_LOD_Sets_Params)' name='federated.0k75y0c1oj9o6d1fipwba1vq21n7' />
            <datasource name='Parameters' />
          </datasources>
          <datasource-dependencies datasource='Parameters'>
            <column caption='Margin Threshold %' datatype='real' name='[Parameter 2]' param-domain-type='range' role='measure' type='quantitative' value='25.'>
              <calculation class='tableau' formula='25.' />
              <range granularity='0.5' min='0.0' />
            </column>
          </datasource-dependencies>
          <datasource-dependencies datasource='federated.0k75y0c1oj9o6d1fipwba1vq21n7'>
            <column caption='Above Threshold' datatype='boolean' name='[Calculation_0279276467589124]' role='dimension' type='nominal'>
              <calculation class='tableau' formula='[Profit_Margin_%] &gt;= [Parameters].[Parameter 2]' />
            </column>
            <column caption='Product Name' datatype='string' name='[Product_Name]' role='dimension' type='nominal' />
            <column caption='Profit Margin %' datatype='real' name='[Profit_Margin_%]' role='measure' type='quantitative' />
            <column datatype='real' name='[Revenue]' role='measure' type='quantitative' />
            <column-instance column='[Profit_Margin_%]' derivation='Avg' name='[avg:Profit_Margin_%:qk]' pivot='key' type='quantitative' />
            <column-instance column='[Calculation_0279276467589124]' derivation='None' name='[none:Calculation_0279276467589124:nk]' pivot='key' type='nominal' />
            <column-instance column='[Product_Name]' derivation='None' name='[none:Product_Name:nk]' pivot='key' type='nominal' />
            <column-instance column='[Revenue]' derivation='Sum' name='[sum:Revenue:qk]' pivot='key' type='quantitative' />
          </datasource-dependencies>
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style>
