                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='10'>N: Software = 5.1% of total revenue (₹3.43M of ₹66.70M) but delivers 20.4% of total profit (₹2.32M of ₹11.39M) — a 4.0× profit multiplier. R: Near‑zero cost of goods sold on digital products turns N: Software = 5.1% of total revenue (₹3.43M of ₹66.70M) but delivers 20.4% of total profit (₹2.32M of ₹11.39M) — a 4.0× profit multiplier. R: Near‑zero cost of goods sold on digital products turns every incremental rupee of Software revenue into ₹0.68 of profit. A: Launch a “Software‑First” procurement template for all new corporate contracts, aiming to double Software’s revenue share to 10% within 12 months, which would add ₹3.2M in pure profit. incremental rupee of Software revenue into ₹0.68 of profit. A: Launch a “Software‑First” procurement template for all new corporate contracts, aiming to double Software’s revenue share to 10% within 12 months, which would add ₹3.2M in pure profit.</run>
